benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: Successful modification with required headers and valid body (TC01).
Optional Headers: Tests include X-Killbill-Reason and X-Killbill-Comment (TC02).
Empty Array Removal: Removing all custom fields (TC03).
Invalid Bundle ID Format: 400 error for malformed ID (TC04).
Non-Existent Bundle: 404 error when bundle not found (TC05).
Missing Required Header: 400 error for missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy (TC06).
Malformed JSON Body: 400 error for bad JSON (TC07).
Missing Request Body: 400 error when body is absent (TC08).
Unsupported Fields: 400 error for extra fields in body (TC09).
Unauthorized Access: 401 error when token missing (TC10).
Service Unavailable: 503 error for dependency failure (TC11).
SQL Injection Prevention: 400 error for malicious value (TC12).
Maximum Allowed Custom Fields: 204 success with max number (TC13).
Maximum Value Length: 204 success with max length value (TC14).
Empty Value: 204 success with empty value (TC15).
Unexpected URL Parameters: 204 success ignoring extra query params (TC16).
Performance Under Normal Load: 204 with <2s response time (TC17).
Performance Under Peak Load: 204 for 100 concurrent requests (TC18).
Regression: Special characters handled correctly (TC19).
Integration: 500 error for inconsistent dependent data (TC20).
Recovery: 204 on retry after transient network failure (TC21).
State Variation - No Existing Fields: 204 creates new fields (TC22).
State Variation - Existing Fields: 204 updates fields (TC23).
State Variation - Partial Update: 204 reflects partial changes (TC24).
Backward Compatibility: 204 for older client version (TC25).
gaps: Concurrency Issues: No tests cover race conditions when multiple users update the same bundle concurrently.
Rate Limiting: No tests verify behavior under rapid successive requests.
Caching Behavior: Not applicable for PUT but no tests for cache headers.
Duplicate Submission: Not applicable for PUT but no tests for idempotency confirmation.
recommendations: Add concurrency tests to ensure race conditions are handled correctly (e.g., two simultaneous PUTs on the same bundle).
Include rate limiting tests to verify the API rejects or throttles excessive requests in a short period.
Consider adding idempotency tests to confirm that repeated identical PUT requests produce the same result without side effects.
